Usage: createWhatIfInternalGeneratedClock [-help] <blackBoxCellName>
                                          -clockName <genClkName>
                                          -clockPin <internalPinName>
                                          [-edge_shift <edge_shift_list>]
                                          [-invert] -masterPin <clockInputPort>
                                          [-noCreateInternalPin] {-multiplyBy <integer> | -divideBy <integer> | -edges <edge_list> }

-help                             # Prints out the command usage
<blackBoxCellName>                # name of the blackbox or blackblob cell
                                  # (string, required)
-clockName <genClkName>           # name of the clock generated on the internal
                                  # pin (string, required)
-clockPin <internalPinName>       # Specifies the name of the pin generated
                                  # inside the blackbox or blackblob
                                  # (string, required)
-divideBy <integer>               # Specifies the frequency division factor
                                  # (int, required)
-edge_shift <edge_shift_list>     # Amount of shift for each edge in -edge_list
                                  # option (string, optional)
-edges <edge_list>                # List of edges from source clock that for
                                  # derived clock (string, optional)
-invert                           # Inverts the source clock (bool, optional)
-masterPin <clockInputPort>       # The source from which the derived clock is
                                  # generated (string, required)
-multiplyBy <integer>             # Specifies the frequency  multiplication
                                  # factor  (int, required)
-noCreateInternalPin              # Specifies that a generated clock should be
                                  # created on an existing internal pin
                                  # (bool, optional)